\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Not a great deal of that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 What about neighbours, did they ever call casually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I wouldn't say call casually but - we did mix with -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did your parents ever go out to visit friends or neighbours, on their own, your mother and father together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Not so much together with father being away but - mother did. Friends and relatives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 What do y
ou think your parents did when they got together with friends and neighbours in the evenings, what kind of amusements, there was no television there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3501630\charrsid2905715 No}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 , it would be largely }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3501630\charrsid2905715 conversation.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715  And occasionally perhaps - a - a - house whist drive. Principally conversation I would say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 
Many people divide society into groups or social classes in the period before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one class or group and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I think that we did. It wasn't - probably wasn't acute. But we had the feeling that there was an upper and a lower - strata.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Would you say there were just the two?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Just the two. I would think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Which strata would you say you belonged to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I would think the - the lower - and it was - I think principally from a financial point of view.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 What sort of people belonged to the same strata as you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 There again - people who belonged to the same strata, I would think people of the similar family income.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 With fathers doing what kind of jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Usually manual work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 What sort of people belonged to the upper strata?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 White collar workers. People with the - a greater income and - and possibly, small private means.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Were you ever told to touch your cap or show respect in some way to people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Just the - the general idea of touching your cap to a lady.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 To every lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Every lady. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Was there anyone that you called sir or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Schoolmasters, schoolmistresses. But apart from that I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents by calling them sir or madam or touching their cap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I don't remember it, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Who were considered the most important people in this area when you were a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 
Well to my mind the - schoolmasters and school and probably the minister of the church. And - certain other people that we came into contact with, perhaps through the Boys Brigade. A visiting inspecting officer. Or people like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 
Why do you think these were considered important, I'm thinking of people who were considered important in the area, not particularly people you - thought were important when you were a boy. People who were generally thought to be quite important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I don't think in the area that we lived that there was anybody that was really considered important. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Why do you think the schoolteachers and people were important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 
I - I think that they - they belonged to that group of people, the white collar worker - in some case the - cased the military rank. And of course the minister of the church was always looked up to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 What about the shopkeepers, can you tell me something about the kind of people they would associate with when they weren't working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 The shopkeepers? I would think other shopkeepers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 How about clergymen, would you say they spent their time with other clergymen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 They did, they had their own fraternal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Schoolteachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Schoolteachers - I would say mixed largely amongst themselves. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 And the employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Yes. Yes. They would mix -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 With themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Yes. Yes. Certain amount of club life too. Where they would be members and where we certainly weren't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 You mean these people would be of the upper strata?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 What sort of people went to the Baptist church that you went to?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Mainly a middle class type of people with a certain element of the schoolmaster type. But I would say mainly middle class people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Are you putting schoolteachers above middle class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 And putting yourself below the middle class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Well I was inclined to think of the two classes you know, more
 or less as upper class and middle. We did use the words upper and lower before. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 So you were middle class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 What about the church of England, would you say that different kinds of people went to that church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 It always seemed 
to me - as thought they were a different type of person, in as - of course the Baptist church in Non-conformist, the Anglican church was being the national church, I think it - it - it governed more people than perhaps the non-conformist church. And for t
hat reason it would have in its congregation - lawyers, doctors, schoolteachers, that sort of folk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 A bit posher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did you know anything about the Catholic congregations for example?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I would say that the Catholic congregation was the more mixed congregation of all. Embracing almost all types.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 
Where you lived did all the people in the middle class have the same standard of living, or would you say there were different groups within the middle class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Oh I think - all most - all of them would be the same standard of living.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 
Could you think of one particular family that you knew that was like your own and tell me something about them, the kind of house they lived in and he clothes they wore and the way they spend their money, is it possible?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 
I can think of one family - that lived quite close to us and - I was very friendly with one of the boys there. And they lived in a - a self contained house. Their income was larger than ours and - they lived on a higher level.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 What was the father's job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 
Father was a hotel manager. And - there were - there was another income also within the home and that meant that their level was higher than ours, and I think that perhaps I was a little bit envious at times. Of th
eir standard. But even so, they - we - we mixed quite freely. But - perhaps I enjoyed myself more there than what my friend enjoyed himself - in my house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 But you would say that you were both middle class families?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I would say we were both middle class families but two - different levels of income.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 How was this expressed, what kind of things did they have that you didn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 They had a more generous table. You see. And the boy himself had - rather more pocket money than I had. But he was 
the lad, you can understand this, who always possessed the football.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Do you think that any families felt themselves superior to others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 It never seemed to be very evident. I think we mixed very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 In the area where you lived as a boy were some families thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Not in the area that I lived. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Would you say they were all respectable or all rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I would say that they were all fairly respectable.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Can you remember a distinction between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I think it was there. But I don't think that it was really pronounced.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different social strata or different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I don't think they altered - their attitude at all. They lived normally wherever they mixed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 You wouldn't find your mother saying, I don't like him he's a bit too stuck up, and your father saying oh yes. I think he's a fine chap?

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 No. I don't think they ever made those observances, certainly not in front of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Do you think your mother as belonging to a particular social strata herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I think I saw my mother, as I always see her, as a very humble person. A very lovable person too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Do you think this is how she looked on herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I think so. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 If she were to use a term like upper class or middle class about herself which term do you think she would use?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Somehow I can't see her using those terms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Was it possible when you were a boy to move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I don't think so. I don't think that it really ever entered in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 You can't think of anyone who went up or down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 No. No. Not in my time as a boy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Can you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Oh I think it applied to - more than one person that I knew. And - more than one person within the knowledge of our family too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Why do you think this kind of term would be applied?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I think for - an essentially good life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 You mean good in the Christian terms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a small boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Very occasionally. If a - a street lamp was broken or something like that, but - there never appeared to be any real ne
ed for the interference of a policeman apart from that. A clip }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3501630\charrsid2905715 around}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715  the ear, something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 What did you think of the policeman?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I think we treated them with a great deal of respect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Were you frightened of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Just a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did your mother ever say when you were naughty, I'll call a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 How do you think that the police treated the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I think they treated them with a - a fair amount of understanding. And they were able to correct quite a number of minor }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3501630\charrsid2905715 misdemeanors}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715  in their own way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 You don't think they were too rough ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I never had any evidence of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Was your home rented or did it belong to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 It was rented.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did you see anything of your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Weekly. As he called for rent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 What did you feel about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Well as soon as ever I could understand the situation I always felt that I would like to own property myself. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Does that mean that you resented him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I didn't resent him but I - I used to think that with a little careful management - rent paying could be avoided.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 What did you think about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I think it created the urge to get away from school and to be a wage earner oneself. To try to help.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 What difference did it make if your father was ill out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 It made - a sufficient difference that at times - we were virtually or almost without money. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 So how did you manage then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Maybe with the help of our maternal grandparents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Was your father ever off work through illness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 No, I think it was - only trough trade disputes or a lack in shipping cargoes or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 And sometimes it went on for a few months, did you ever get help from the Guardians or the parish or any charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Help from the Guardians as they were so}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3501630\charrsid2905715 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 called in that day was a very meager thing indeed - possibly two an sixpence. And it was 
so low and one felt so demeaned having to go for it that we never approached them. Although there were times possibly when we could have done with this assistance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did you get any other help from any other charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Just your relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Relatives, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Do you remember anyone in the district who people disapproved of very strongly and of people taking }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3501630\charrsid2905715 action}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715  against somebody because they disapproved of their way of life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Not in the area where we lived in Birchington Avenue.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Were you given lessons by one of your parents, a tutor or a governess when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Five. Approximately.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 When you first started what time of the morning did you go and when did you come back?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 As clearly as I can remember it would be nine o'clock in the morning and - finishing about half past four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Quite a long day wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 And you started afternoon school right from the beginning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 The whole day school, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 What kind of school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 An ordinary elementary school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Was it boys and girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Yes. Boys and girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 In the first instance - well always I walked. But - until I was twelve years old it was only a very short distance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 About how long did it take you to get there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 The first school I attended it would take me maybe - ten minutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Who did you go with when you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Oh with any neighbour's child of approximately the same age as myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Where did you have hour midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 At home. Always at home. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I enjoyed it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 And what did you think about the teachers, how did you fell about them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I think - reasonably friendly. I didn't incur their wrath too often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did they emphasise certain things as being important in life?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 The only teacher that I ever remember emphasising anything was - that I should always take care of my voice. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Why do you think that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 
He was to invite me out to the front of the class and - ask me to tell them a story. And I used to have to tall them something just - out of imagination.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 He thought you were good at this did he, he liked the sound of your voice and your imagination?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Yes. And not long after that I had a paper round.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 You were caned. It was always that. Cane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Girls and boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I th
ink so, yes, I don't know - positively about that because of course they weren't mixed classes. No, they were separate parts of the school. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 It wasn't a completely mixed school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Not completely, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 What kind of offences would you be caned for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I think }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3501630\charrsid2905715 principally}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715  for playing the fool in the classroom and being just a wee bit unruly. And of course for - for bad work. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did your parents show any interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 They did. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did they ask what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Yes. They were interested and concerned about your progress.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did they ever visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 It wasn't the usual custom in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did they meet the teachers, did they know the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Not unless there was some specific reason.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did the other children at your school come from similar types of home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Broadly speaking, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did you remember the teachers ever singling out children for special treatment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Not until latter years - when you were approaching school leaving age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 What happened then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 
I was one - and we were contained in a particular class where we got an advanced education with a view to taking the Oxford preliminary examination. Which was equivalent to matriculation certificate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 How many of you were in this special class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 There - this was then a mixed class, girls and boys, and I would think there'd probably be - forty to fifty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 In this special class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 In this - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 How many others who weren't in this class but were of the same age?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Oh well, there were several classes. The number of the students I - I couldn't say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Do you remember any gangs or groups in your school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 No. Apart from - soccer groups. And that sort of thing. In the - the 
- round what you played, you see, you formed a team. But not in the gang sense.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Do you remember any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Only through - through inability to play sports. Through some physical defect perhaps, that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did you go on to another school afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 That was the school where we were in the advanced class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 You were in school when you were five?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 What was the name of this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Leegate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 How long did you stay in that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 
Only two or three years, yes. Then we went on to another elementary school which was Mortimer Road. And I was there until I was twelve. And then to Western Central school which was a small fee paying school. And it was there that we received - tho
se who were sufficiently advanced - we received this education for the Oxford Preliminary Examination.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Do you know what the fees were at this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I don't think they were more than about thirty shillings a year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 You stayed there from the age of twelve 'til ....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did you take this exam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 How did you get on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I qualified in about seven or eight subjects I think and received the certificate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 And then you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Left school, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3501630\charrsid2905715 Did you ever go to any other school?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Would you have stayed longer if you'd had the chance to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I would have liked to stayed longer and to have been able to specialise.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did you attend any part time education afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 No. Not apart from my own reading.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 And evening classes for example?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I didn't attend any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Not real regrets, apart from the fact I would have - I would have liked to continue.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Very much so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 While you were at school did you have a part time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I had a paper round. Yes. Where we used to shout the papers. Shout, you know, Special Gazette, go round the streets and shout, you d
idn't have - regular - you might have had one or two regular customers but you actually sold them on the streets Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 How did you get this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 You were allowed to go - buy a certain quantity of papers which you got at a reduced rate and - then 
go round the streets and sell them. And you made a small profit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 So for example you'd buy them at a ha'penny and all them at a penny?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Or whatever - that's right, yes. Actually you bought them at so much a dozen and then sold them singly. And you
 could make - if you had a reasonable round you might make - say, five or six shillings in a week. It was - instrumental in - in the income of a family which was small. Or the income was small.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 What hours did you work at this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 After school hours from about - half past five 'til you'd sold your papers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did you work Sundays and Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 No. Saturdays, yes, not Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 What hours on Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Approximately the same hours, excepting you might have the ordinary evening paper and a football edition.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 You earn about five shillings a week did you say?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 About five shillings a week, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did you think that was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Oh we thought it was tremendous.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did you give any of the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 All of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Do you know what it was spent on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Just on the ordinary home living and - put in with the general income.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 How did you get on with the other people that you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Very well indeed. We were a chummy lot as newsboys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 What about your employer, how did he treat you, whoever he was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Well, we were simply one of a fairly big group. Buying papers from which was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3501630\charrsid2905715 distribution}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715  centre you see. I don't suppose he knew us any more than that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 How did you feel about him, did you have any particular feelings towards him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Only that he was the source of our income.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 How about the work, did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I don't think we disliked it. Except in the bad weather. And - a friendly bunch of newsboys that - oh I think we got a kick out of it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Do you think this job altered your attitude to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Not in that sense, I don't think so, it - it simply - brought home to me that - we simply had to be wage earners. As quickly as possible.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did you do any other part time jobs after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 How did you get your first full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 It was a job that was advertised and I applied. Along with - I think about six other boys. And it was for a junior clerk in an }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3501630\charrsid2905715 accountant\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715  office.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 And what exactly did you have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 We were interviewed by the chartered accountant himself and then he made the selection.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 And when you started work what did you do exactly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3501630\charrsid2905715 Principally}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715  addressing envelopes. Then goi
ng on to checking of accounts in audit work and - general junior clerk office duties.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 And what hours did you work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Nine in the morning and supposedly to about half past five, but several times I worked until about seven. For no extra remuneration.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Because you were forced to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 No, the - the volume of work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did you feel free so say, I must go now, it's half past five?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I wouldn't have dared.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 You felt obliged to stay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did you work Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Saturday mornings. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Ever in the afternoons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Never in the afternoons, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did you have a half day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Saturday afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did you get paid for holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Paid for holidays yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 How long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 One week.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 How much were you paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Three and sixpence per week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Less than you made on the papers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did you feel that was a fair wage or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I felt that it was a starting point.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did you give this money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did that go in the housekeeping the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 That went in with housekeeping, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 How did you get on with the people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Very well indeed. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 And your employer, how did he treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 He treated me very well - considering that he h
ad a boy who was called Stanley and who had just recently died. And for that reason I nearly didn't get the job. Didn't see how they could call me Stanley.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Because you'd be about the same age would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Yes. And I asked him, well how did I get t
he job? Sir. He said, you're the only boy that came in and said, good morning sir. We all had the same qualifications Oxford certificates. There you are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did you like your employer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I did. Yes. I liked every part of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 What about the work you were doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I liked that. I would have liked to have }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3501630\charrsid2905715 specialized}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715  as an accountant or perhaps have gone into medicine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 How long did you stay in that particular job?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Two years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 And then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 And I went into a - a retail store.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 As what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 As a - a junior assistant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Was this that clothes shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 You stayed there for how long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Fifty years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 From 1916 until 1966?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 1965 and a half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Were you a junior clerk all this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 No. No.
 I went - I went through every department of the retail store. After a while I assisted, because of previous experience, I assisted with the clerical work which stood me in good stead until I became - assistant secretary and then afterwards I became compa
ny secretary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 You were an important man then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I used to like to think so. Had a hell of a lot of work I know. Oh, that's on the tape.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Would you have preferred any other kind of job if you'd had the chance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I - I'm not grumbling at the 
job that I had because I qualified very well in it, but I would have liked to specialise either in accountancy I think, of medicine. And I would have liked sufficient time to study music.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Are you still a keen musician then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I don't get the opportunity for playing very much at all now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did you serve any apprenticeship or training period for any of your jobs?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 No. No. That - that was the bugbear, that you had to be articled to become an accountant. And it meant an articled fee of a hundr
ed and fifty to two hundred pounds. And - it was - the restrictive side perhaps of accountancy that I couldn't enter into that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did you belong to any trade union or professional organisation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did you feel that employers and workers had the same interests or different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3501630\charrsid2905715 With the firm that I worked I found that the employers and the employees were very, very close together. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 With kindred interests, thinking of each other and helping each other. Otherwise I would never have stayed fifty years with one firm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did you think that among workers there were divisions of interest? Workers in general?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 No. No. I would think that there are divisions of interest - and it applied even as - even in a - the smaller type of concern in whic
h I worked. It would be there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 
Some people say that in the period before 1918 there was a great division between craftsmen and other workers, did you thing there was a great division between craftsmen and other workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I was never really conscious of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Would you say that full time work changed your attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 It made me feel more responsible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did you continue to live at home after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did starting full time work change your relationship with your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 What about your relationship with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 That remained just the same. It altered times of course but that didn't interfere with the relationship.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Were Sundays any different after you'd left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 No. Still continued with church work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did you have any political views at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Not pronounced.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Why do you think you had no political views at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I think that there are so many good points in either of the leading parties.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did you ever feel under any pressure from anybody to vote for a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 For example, your employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did you ever belong to a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did you ever work for any party at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Only for local government. When my employer was standing to be a councilor in his particular ward and I helped in that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did he represent any particular party or was he an independent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 He - he represented the - the Moderates.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Was it called the moderate party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 It was called the Rent and Ratepayers in those days, yes, but it was a moderate party. Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Apart from that did you ever take part in any political activity at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Never. I never even attended a political meeting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did you continue to spend your spare time in the same way after you left school or did you do different things then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 
I - very much in the same way, I still played tennis and badminton. I founded a badminton club. I spent a fair amount of time in the evenings dancing. Rowing, swimming, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did you go out in the evenings after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Occasionally to a show.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 What type of show?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 
The picture house or - a theatre, Empire theatre, with variety turns. And - celebrity concerts. Which I attended in Newcastle and I think there were about seven or eight of those in a year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 What kind of celebrity concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Leading pianists, Padorevsky, leading singers, violinists, orchestras and so forth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Who did you go with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Sometimes with my choirmaster and - sometimes - with a friend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did you make any new friends at this time, just after you'd left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Yes. Yes, I made a few new friends through dancing classes, badminton, tennis.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did you ever bring your friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Yes. Yes. Male. Male friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 How's that then, was your mother very strict?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 No, no. No, I was careful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did you have any special friends in the period when you were about fourteen to eighteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Not really. I think just a small group that moved round together.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Apart from theatres and things did you ever go out anywhere else with this small group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Just to these dancing classes and dances proper. Tennis, badminton, occasional picnics too in the summertime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 So your parents met your male friends but not your female friends, did they expect to know where you were when you went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I was never seriously }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3501630\charrsid2905715 criticised}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715  or questioned. I think they had faith in me, do think that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Did you have to be home by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 I wasn't really interested in staying out late but they expected me to be home in reasonable time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 What did they think was reasonable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Not later than approximately ten o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4725300 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 How old were you when you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11864399 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6046477\charrsid2905715 Thirty-two.
